.TH "firmware_data_write" 9 "firmware_data_write" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
firmware_data_write \- write method for firmware
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "ssize_t" firmware_data_write
.BI "(struct file *filp "  ","
.BI "struct kobject *kobj "  ","
.BI "struct bin_attribute *bin_attr "  ","
.BI "char *buffer "  ","
.BI "loff_t offset "  ","
.BI "size_t count "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "filp" 12
open sysfs file
.IP "kobj" 12
kobject for the device
.IP "bin_attr" 12
bin_attr structure
.IP "buffer" 12
buffer being written
.IP "offset" 12
buffer offset for write in total data store area
.IP "count" 12
buffer size

Data written to the 'data' attribute will be later handed to
the driver as a firmware image.
